Please inform us of any change in your mailing address 30 days in advance of the change. If you are selling your property, please have your lawyer
Moving
forward us a standard "Lawyer's Letter". If there is a remaining term on the rental equipment contract, two options are available. Either the new
owner can sign an assumption agreement or @home Energy will invoice you the balance of the contract.
Cancellation of Account
If at any time you request a cancellation and the rental equipment needs to be removed from the property, a close out fee will be applied to your
final bill. The standard removal charge will be billed as follows: (1) our account closure charge of $50.00 will be applied if the water heater is
disconnected and drained by a qualified contractor; (2) our account closure and disconnect charge of $100.00 will be applied, if the water heater is
not disconnected and drained by a qualified contractor. Due to safety concerns and regulations, equipment cannot be returned to the @home
Energy office. Please contact our office for more details, 705-675-0525.
Owners with Rental Property
The landlord/owner of rental property is legally responsible for payment of the rental equipment in the event a tenant defaults in payment. If
payment is not received, @home Energy will advise the tenant through a collection notice 15 days after the billing due date and then again at 30
days. If payment is still not received after 45 days of issuing the second notice, the account will automatically transfer into the property owner's
name. It is the owner's responsibility to remit payment on the outstanding arrears. Please know that @home Energy will do our utmost to collect

payment from the tenant by way of collection notices.
